1.   A political unit, such as a city, town, or village, incorporated for local self-government. 2.   A body of officials appointed to manage the affairs of a local political unit. 1.   (Government, Politics & Diplomacy) a city, town, or district enjoying some degree of local self-government 2.   (Government, Politics & Diplomacy) the governing body of such a unit    1.   a city, town, village, or borough possessing corporate existence and usu. its own local government.     2.   the governing body of such a district. 